   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">If the system needs to be stored a short time after delivery but
before installation, the system should be stored in the transportation
crate with the sealed inner packing intact.</p>
      <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Batteries have different storage requirements
than systems and depends on, for example, type, charge and manufacturer.
If the batteries have to be stored after delivery but before installation
the requirements of the original equipment manufacturer (OEM) have
to be followed.</note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">System storage environment:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Temperature:</p>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Recommended: -10°C to +55°C (+14°F to +131°F)</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Allowable min/max: -20°C to +70°C (-4°F to +158°F)<fn class="- topic/fn "> For aluminum foil vacuum sealed packing with indicator instruments
the allowable min/max is +5°C to +60°C (+40°F to +140°F)</fn>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Relative humidity: 0–95% Non-condensing</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">If the system needs to be stored for a longer time the system have
to be stored according to the specifications and instructions in the
chapter <xref href="Storage_of_the_System_CPT_0000356482.dita"
               scope="local"
               type="concept"
               class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
